<Link id="l00430" /><CodeLine lineNumber="430"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00531" /><CodeLine lineNumber="531"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00532" /><CodeLine lineNumber="532"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Callback type for ExecutionSession lookups.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00533" /><CodeLine lineNumber="533"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00543" /><CodeLine lineNumber="543"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; names that they wish to hold after the function returns.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00549" /><CodeLine lineNumber="549"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00550" /><CodeLine lineNumber="550"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Look up symbols in an execution session.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00551" /><CodeLine lineNumber="551"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00552" /><CodeLine lineNumber="552"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; This is a wrapper around the general ExecutionSession::lookup function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00553" /><CodeLine lineNumber="553"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00554" /><CodeLine lineNumber="554"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The SearchOrder argument contains a list of (JITDylibs, JITDylibSearchFlags)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00555" /><CodeLine lineNumber="555"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; pairs that describe the search order. The JITDylibs will be searched in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00556" /><CodeLine lineNumber="556"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; given order to try to find the symbols in the Symbols argument.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00557" /><CodeLine lineNumber="557"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00558" /><CodeLine lineNumber="558"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The Symbols argument should contain a null-terminated array of</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00559" /><CodeLine lineNumber="559"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; (SymbolStringPtr, SymbolLookupFlags) pairs describing the symbols to be</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00560" /><CodeLine lineNumber="560"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; searched for. This function takes ownership of the elements of the Symbols</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00561" /><CodeLine lineNumber="561"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; array. The Name fields of the Symbols elements are taken to have been</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00562" /><CodeLine lineNumber="562"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; retained by the client for this function. The client should &#42;not&#42; release the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00563" /><CodeLine lineNumber="563"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Name fields, but are still responsible for destroying the array itself.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00564" /><CodeLine lineNumber="564"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00565" /><CodeLine lineNumber="565"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The HandleResult function will be called once all searched for symbols have</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00566" /><CodeLine lineNumber="566"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; been found, or an error occurs. The HandleResult function will be passed an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00567" /><CodeLine lineNumber="567"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; LLVMErrorRef indicating success or failure, and (on success) a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00568" /><CodeLine lineNumber="568"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; null-terminated LLVMOrcCSymbolMapPairs array containing the function result,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00569" /><CodeLine lineNumber="569"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; and the Ctx value passed to the lookup function.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00570" /><CodeLine lineNumber="570"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00571" /><CodeLine lineNumber="571"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The client is fully responsible for managing the lifetime of the Ctx object.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00572" /><CodeLine lineNumber="572"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; A common idiom is to allocate the context prior to the lookup and deallocate</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00573" /><CodeLine lineNumber="573"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; it in the handler.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00574" /><CodeLine lineNumber="574"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00632" /><CodeLine lineNumber="632"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00633" /><CodeLine lineNumber="633"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Name is a name for this MaterializationUnit to be used for identification</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00634" /><CodeLine lineNumber="634"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; and logging purposes (e.g. if this MaterializationUnit produces an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00635" /><CodeLine lineNumber="635"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; object buffer then the name of that buffer will be derived from this name).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00636" /><CodeLine lineNumber="636"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00637" /><CodeLine lineNumber="637"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The Syms list contains the names and linkages of the symbols provided by this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00638" /><CodeLine lineNumber="638"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; unit. This function takes ownership of the elements of the Syms array. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00639" /><CodeLine lineNumber="639"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Name fields of the array elements are taken to have been retained for this</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00640" /><CodeLine lineNumber="640"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; function. The client should &#42;not&#42; release the elements of the array, but is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00641" /><CodeLine lineNumber="641"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; still responsible for destroying the array itself.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00642" /><CodeLine lineNumber="642"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00643" /><CodeLine lineNumber="643"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The InitSym argument indicates whether or not this MaterializationUnit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00644" /><CodeLine lineNumber="644"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; contains static initializers. If three are no static initializers (the common</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00645" /><CodeLine lineNumber="645"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; case) then this argument should be null. If there are static initializers</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00646" /><CodeLine lineNumber="646"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; then InitSym should be set to a unique name that also appears in the Syms</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00647" /><CodeLine lineNumber="647"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; list with the LLVMJITSymbolGenericFlagsMaterializationSideEffectsOnly flag</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00648" /><CodeLine lineNumber="648"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; set. This function takes ownership of the InitSym, which should have been</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00649" /><CodeLine lineNumber="649"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; retained twice on behalf of this function: once for the Syms entry and once</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00650" /><CodeLine lineNumber="650"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; for InitSym. If clients wish to use the InitSym value after this function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00651" /><CodeLine lineNumber="651"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; returns they must retain it once more for themselves.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00652" /><CodeLine lineNumber="652"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00653" /><CodeLine lineNumber="653"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; If any of the symbols in the Syms list is looked up then the Materialize</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00654" /><CodeLine lineNumber="654"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; function will be called.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00655" /><CodeLine lineNumber="655"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00656" /><CodeLine lineNumber="656"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; If any of the symbols in the Syms list is overridden then the Discard</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00657" /><CodeLine lineNumber="657"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; function will be called.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00658" /><CodeLine lineNumber="658"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00659" /><CodeLine lineNumber="659"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The caller owns the underling MaterializationUnit and is responsible for</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00660" /><CodeLine lineNumber="660"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; either passing it to a JITDylib (via LLVMOrcJITDylibDefine) or disposing</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00661" /><CodeLine lineNumber="661"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; of it by calling LLVMOrcDisposeMaterializationUnit.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00662" /><CodeLine lineNumber="662"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;/</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00999" /><CodeLine lineNumber="999"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/&#42;&#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01000" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1000"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Get a DynamicLibrarySearchGenerator that will reflect process symbols into</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01001" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1001"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; the JITDylib. On success the resulting generator is owned by the client.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1002"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; Ownership is typically transferred by adding the instance to a JITDylib</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01003" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1003"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; using LLVMOrcJITDylibAddGenerator,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01004" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1004"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01005" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1005"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The GlobalPrefix argument specifies the character that appears on the front</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1006"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; of linker-mangled symbols for the target platform (e.g. &#39;&#95;&#39; on MachO).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1007"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; If non-null, this character will be stripped from the start of all symbol</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1008"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; strings before passing the remaining substring to dlsym.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1009"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1010"><span class="doxyHighlightComment"> &#42; The optional Filter and Ctx arguments can be used to supply a symbol name</span></CodeLine>
